theorem Topology.P1_iUnion {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Sort _} {S : ι → Set X}
    (hS : ∀ i, Topology.P1 (A := S i)) :
    Topology.P1 (A := ⋃ i, S i) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at *
  intro x hx
  rcases mem_iUnion.1 hx with ⟨i, hx_i⟩
  have hx_closure : x ∈ closure (interior (S i)) := hS i hx_i
  have h_subset : closure (interior (S i)) ⊆ closure (interior (⋃ j, S j)) := by
    have h_int_subset : interior (S i) ⊆ interior (⋃ j, S j) := by
      have h_sub : (S i : Set X) ⊆ ⋃ j, S j := by
        intro y hy
        exact mem_iUnion.2 ⟨i, hy⟩
      exact interior_mono h_sub
    exact closure_mono h_int_subset
  exact h_subset hx_closure

theorem Topology.P1_closureInterior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    Topology.P1 (A := closure (interior A)) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hx
  -- Show the required inclusion of closures of interiors.
  have h_inclusion : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
    -- First, `interior A` is contained in `closure (interior A)`,
    -- so interiors are monotone with respect to this inclusion.
    have h_int : interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
      have h_sub : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
        intro y hy; exact subset_closure hy
      exact interior_mono h_sub
    -- Taking closures preserves set inclusion.
    exact closure_mono h_int
  exact h_inclusion hx

theorem Topology.P1_implies_P1_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 (A := A)) : Topology.P1 (A := closure A) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1 ⊢
  intro x hx_closureA
  -- First, use `hP1` to see that `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have hA : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
    have : closure A ⊆ closure (closure (interior A)) := closure_mono hA
    simpa [closure_closure] using this
  -- Next, note that `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := interior_mono subset_closure
    exact closure_mono this
  -- Chain the inclusions to reach the desired membership.
  exact h₂ (h₁ hx_closureA)
